    <b>HORIZONS Developer Diary</b><br>
    <font size=1><b>Date:</b> Friday, March 16 @ 11:38:05 EST<br><b>Topic:</b> Beta Test News<br><br>
    </center><font size=2>
    <a href="http://rpgplanet.com">RPGPlanet</a> have a <a href="http://rpgplanet.com/features/articles/diary_horizons">Developer Diary</a> from David Allen, the CEO of Artifact Entertainment who currently developing the massively multiplayer, online RPG HORIZONS: Empires of Isteria. I Spy > Beta: 
<br>
<br>
<i>It's one thing to talk about how great HORIZONS is going to be, and what kind of features it's going to support - it's another to implement it. Surprising enough, we are on track for nearly every feature that was originally designed - the game is going to be incredible. I wish I could go into some detail with some of the specific and unique features of the game, but I can't as of yet - we'll be announcing these 'unannounced' features around the time that public BETA starts (no specific date as of yet  [Source: <a href="http://www.betabites.com/">Beta Bites</a>]</i>
